# k8s/svc-export/gcs-sa.yaml.example
# ===========================================================================
# svc-export — Sub-Plan A (export extraction), INFRA deliverable I6.
#
# GCS Service Account SPEC for the export path prefix. REFERENCE/SPEC ONLY —
# this is NOT a kubectl-appliable manifest (GCS SAs are a GCP IAM concern,
# created via Terraform + applied by the founder; the org policy forbids SA JSON
# keys so there is NO k8s Secret to apply).
#
# Authority: handoff_msA_infra.md §1 I6 + MASTER_PLAN §2.E ("Each service that
# touches GCS (image-svc, export-svc) gets its own GCP Service Account with
# storage.objectAdmin on its path prefix. No bucket split in V1.5.").
#
# ── SCOPE GUARD (Sub-Plan A constraint §4) ─────────────────────────────────
#   This authorizes EXACTLY ONE new GCP Service Account (the export workload SA)
#   with storage.objectAdmin SCOPED to the exports path prefix. Anything bigger —
#   a new bucket, a new IAM role beyond this one SA, project-level grants — is
#   OUT OF SCOPE: STOP and flag to the founder. Do NOT execute.
#
# ── AUTH MODEL: KEYLESS (GCE metadata server) ──────────────────────────────
#   The org policy constraints/iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation (org
#   698205129974) FORBIDS SA JSON keys. So:
#     - There is NO k8s Secret holding a key.json.
#     - GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS is ABSENT from the svc-export pods.
#     - The pod inherits a GCP identity via the GCE metadata server (169.254.169.254)
#       on the K3s node.
#
#   TWO viable bindings (founder/TF picks one at apply):
#
#   (A) V1.5 SIMPLEST — reuse the node's VM SA (current monolith pattern).
#       The K3s node VM SA `888244156264-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com`
#       ALREADY has roles/storage.objectAdmin on gs://meesell-prod-assets (Phase A
#       A2, mirrored by image-precheck's meesell-images bucket). svc-export pods on
#       the node inherit it transparently — ZERO new IAM. Path-prefix tenancy is
#       enforced in APPLICATION code (export_service writes only under
#       exports/{user_id}/{export_id}.xlsx), NOT by IAM. This is the ₹0, no-new-SA
#       path and is RECOMMENDED for Sub-Plan A (dev, zero-traffic).
#
#   (B) V1.5 HARDENED (MASTER_PLAN §2.E target) — a DEDICATED export workload SA
#       bound to the K8s ServiceAccount via Workload Identity, with
#       storage.objectAdmin granted via an IAM Condition scoping it to the
#       `exports/` prefix. This is the "own SA per GCS-touching service" target.
#       It requires Workload Identity wiring on K3s (kubelet credential provider) —
#       deferred per MEMORY (Phase E follow-up) and per infra plan MS-K8S-4 (L,
#       V1.5 hardening, NOT the Sub-Plan-A default per R-MS-6).
#
#   DECISION for Sub-Plan A: take (A) — inherit the node VM SA, app-layer prefix
#   tenancy, ₹0, no new IAM. The dedicated-SA (B) ships with MS-K8S-4 when Workload
#   Identity lands on the cluster. This keeps Sub-Plan A within "the one export SA"
#   ceiling (here: zero new SAs — even tighter than the ceiling).
#
# ── PATH PREFIX ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Bucket: gs://meesell-prod-assets (single-bucket SSOT, Phase A / MEMORY D1).
#   Export objects: exports/{user_id}/{export_id}.xlsx  (and …/{export_id}.zip for
#   xlsx_with_images). This matches the live GCS_BUCKET + the export_service GCS
#   write path. (The handoff/MASTER_PLAN write `meesell-exports/{user_id}/...` as a
#   logical name; the live single-bucket SSOT realizes it as the `exports/` prefix
#   inside meesell-prod-assets — D1 reconciliation, MEMORY 2026-06-08.)
#
# ── TERRAFORM (when option B is taken at V1.5) ──────────────────────────────
#   New module infra/terraform/modules/svc_export_gcs_sa/ (NOT authored/applied in
#   Sub-Plan A — option A needs no module):
#     resource "google_service_account" "svc_export"            # export workload SA
#     resource "google_storage_bucket_iam_member" "svc_export"  # objectAdmin w/ IAM
#                                                               # Condition on prefix
#                                                               # "exports/"
#     resource "google_service_account_iam_member" "wi_binding" # WI: KSA → GSA
#   Apply: terraform apply -target=module.svc_export_gcs_sa  (founder-run).
#
# ── ENV (set regardless of A/B; non-secret, from meesell-config) ────────────
#   GCS_BUCKET=meesell-prod-assets
#   GCS_PROJECT_ID=project-1f5cbf72-2820-4cdb-949
#   GCS_SIGNED_URL_TTL_SECONDS=3600   (export poll returns 1-hour signed URLs)
#   (NO GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS — keyless.)
#
# Cost impact: ₹0 (option A reuses the existing node SA + existing bucket; export
# object storage is immaterial at V1 volume).
# ===========================================================================
